jobs.description:
Why Join Us

Yotta’s huge fanbase has helped turn us into a globally ranked game developer with offices worldwide. Despite our success, at heart we are still players trying to create exciting and engaging, never-before-experienced games. That drive to make games that we want to play is what animates our well-resourced, ambitious, creative team members. Working together in a supportive, open... workplace and taking cues from our gaming communities, we create products that entertain the world.

Responsibilities

As a Senior Physics Programmer you will play a crucial role in the creation and upkeep of physically based features. Together, you and our engineering and design team will be in charge of delivering and integrating solid physical behaviors while utilizing and improving underlying physics engines to satisfy a variety of intricate project requirements. You will be key to achieving the ideal balance between fun and realism in terms of the game's vehicles and weapons.

What You’ll Be Doing:
• Support and collaborate cross-functionally to implement complex game features;
• Research subject matter relating to objectives to ensure an authentic experience;
• Troubleshoot technical and artistic issues;
• Communicate effectively with team members, production and management to ensure that project goals are met;
• Contribute to high quality look development with the goal of setting the bar;
• Ensure the technical approach being proposed for a given feature satisfies both the surface-level, and deeper, engineering-specific requirements;
• Be a proactive self-starter that can independently implement high-level direction;
• Champion standard methodologies and advocate towards streamlining tools and processes;
• Contribute creative and original ideas towards all aspects of game production and development.

Qualifications

We Expect You To Have:
• 5+ years’ experience in developing games professionally;
• Experience with simulation or physics systems in a game engine; including tools pipeline, performance optimization, behavior, etc.;
• Knowledge of rigid, multi body simulation and Newtonian mechanics;
• Strong math skills (linear algebra, trigonometry, matrix/quaternion math); skills and the ability to code and architect gameplay mechanics and tools;
• Excellent understanding of Physically Based Rendering systems and techniques;
• Possesses in-depth understanding of game engines, pipelines, and processes;
• Passion for physics and making physics work in the game world;
• The capacity to flourish in a demanding and frequently ambiguous workplace, strong work ethic, independent working abilities, effective communication, and strong problem-solving skills.

Even Better If You Have:
• Experience in shipping AAA games;
• Experience in open world games;
• Experience in Unreal 4/5.

Additional Information
• This is a hybrid role based in Los Angeles (currently hybrid because of pandemic);
• Current working hours: Monday – Friday, 11am – 8pm Pacific Time (including one-hour break);
• Salary depending on experience.

Yotta is committed to building an inclusive environment where creative professionals from a multitude of diverse cultural backgrounds collaborate to inspire audiences and each other. We are passionately supportive of equality in all its forms and never discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, orientation, identity, national origin, handicap, or any other category protected by applicable federal and state law
